# slipway-init

- Trigger: {{.Trigger}}
- Description: Initialize Slipway in the current project

Command:
```bash
slipway init --tools all
```

This command is setup-only and executes the CLI directly.
No skill routing is required.

## Flags
- `--tools <all|none|comma list>`: tool adapters to generate (e.g. `claude,codex,cursor,opencode`); `all` generates every adapter, `none` initializes only the runtime layout (`.slipway.yaml`, gitignore block, runtime markers) with no adapter files.
- `--refresh`: regenerate managed tool artifacts deterministically. When `--tools` is omitted, `--refresh` auto-detects previously generated adapters and reports a remediation if none are found.
{{- end -}}
